===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|庚|米|t1=threshing tools|t2=rice|ls=ic}} – chaff. The clearest version is [[𢊪]], in which the two components can be identified well; in the semi-conservative variant [[𥹺]], the rice at the bottom is still well visible. The derivative {{zh-l|*糠}} refers to the original word.

Unrelated to [[隶]], in which the bottom part is a reference to a tail ([[毛]]); also unrelated to [[水]].

===Etymology===
; quiet, calm, peaceful
: {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} compares {{och-l|康|tr=*khâŋ}} < *''khlaŋ'' to {{cog|lus|tlan}} ~ {{m|lus|tlang||good, kindly, mild, calm, etc.}}, both tentatively from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*klaŋ}}.
; Kham
: Borrowed from {{bor|zh|bo|ཁམས}}.
; "to look, to see"
: Arose from mishearing of {{zh-l|好康|[[rich]]; [[lucky]]; [[fortunate]]}} as {{zh-l|好看|[[good-looking]]; [[worth]] [[see]]ing}} in a line of {{lw|zh|如果早知道男生也會被性侵|pref=《|suf=》}}.

